text: Zakerana sauriceps (lizard-headed frog or Mysore wart frog) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats, India. It is only known from its type locality, Wattekole in Kodagu district, Karnataka state. ==References== sauriceps Category:Frogs of India Category:Endemic fauna of the Western Ghats Category:Taxa named by C.
